#Usage:
#------
video gif [files] [--text-top TEXT] [--text-bottom TEXT] [--font-size SIZE]

#Description:
#------------
Convert a video into an animated GIF using ffmpeg.  
Optionally add meme-style white text at the top and/or bottom.  
If no parameters are provided, an interactive mode is started.

#Text Options:
#-------------
--text-top           Add text at the top of the GIF
--text-bottom        Add text at the bottom of the GIF
--font-size          Font size of the text (default: medium)
                     Choices: small, medium, large

#Interactive Mode:
#-----------------
If no input files are provided, you will be asked to:
 - select the video file interactively
 - enter optional top and bottom text (leave blank to skip)
 - choose a font size: small, medium or large

#Output:
#-------
- GIF is created in the same folder with `.gif` extension
- The result will loop infinitely (`-loop 0`)
- GIF opens automatically with the default viewer

#Font Handling:
#--------------
- The script attempts to use the system-installed "Impact" font
- If not available, it falls back to `impact.ttf` in the script folder
- Make sure `impact.ttf` is present if system font is missing

#Examples:
#---------
video gif clip.mp4
video gif funny.mov --text-top "WHEN YOU CODE" --text-bottom "AND IT WORKS"
video gif scene.mp4 --text-bottom "EPIC MOMENT" --font-size large

#Notes:
#------
- Recommended input formats: mp4, mkv, mov
- Output resolution is scaled to 320px width with preserved aspect ratio
- Frame rate is fixed at 10 fps for reasonable file size

